= Startup =

To startup the Window Manager in a new X session run:

  sh startx.sh

This command will open a new X server on a new display with a terminal.
When you want to close X and return to the original display just `exit'
the shell in the terminal.

= WM instructions =

The window manager in Wm.st has been written by Rahul aka blufox,
inspired by tinywm.

To drag a window, press ALT and the sx mouse button, then move.

To resize a window, press ALT and the dx mouse button, then move.

To raise a window, press F1 on the window.
